Description: Fragment of oval handle to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-brown; cream slip. Circular stamp with Helios head symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink '7̣5', not deleted. Name Euphranor. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0360.35.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (147)
